<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="115" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Diagnostic description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
Overall dark brown. Pronotal disc (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. Costalampys quadriguttata (Gorham) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antenna, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Sternum IX, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543223" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">20A, F</figureCitation>
) dark brown, lacking vittae, pronotal expansions somewhat translucent anteriorly, almost entirely pale yellow, except by posterior margin, which is outlined in brown, blending with the dark brown disc color. Elytron (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. Costalampys quadriguttata (Gorham) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antenna, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Sternum IX, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543223" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">20B</figureCitation>
) brown, with a pale yellow longitudinal stripe about 1/3
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as elytra, with a roundish spot at posterior 3/4, reaching inner suture, about a 1/3
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as wide as elytra. Legs brown, except for trochanters and metacoxa, which are light brown. Sternum VIII (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. Costalampys quadriguttata (Gorham) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antenna, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Sternum IX, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543223" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">20G</figureCitation>
) entirely translucent. Pygidium (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. Costalampys quadriguttata (Gorham) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antenna, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Sternum IX, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543223" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">20H</figureCitation>
) entirely translucent.
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543223" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" start="Figure 20" startId="F20">
