<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
Pronotum (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. Costalampys quadriguttata (Gorham) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antenna, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Sternum IX, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543223" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">20F</figureCitation>
) with sides rounded, divergent posteriorly. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Male.</emphasis>
Total length = 11.1-11.9 mm (aver. 11.5 mm); Pronotal length = 2.5 mm; Pronotal width = 4.0-4.2 mm (aver. 4.1 mm); Elytral length = 9.0 mm; Elytral width = 2.9-3.0 mm (aver. 2.95 mm). Antennomere III (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. Costalampys quadriguttata (Gorham) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antenna, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Sternum IX, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543223" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">20E</figureCitation>
) with lamella about 2
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than core antennomere. Sternum VI (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. Costalampys quadriguttata (Gorham) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antenna, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Sternum IX, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543223" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">20B</figureCitation>
) with lantern of moderate size, occupying the medial 1.4 of the sternum, almost reaching its anterior margin. Sterna VI and VII (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. Costalampys quadriguttata (Gorham) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antenna, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Sternum IX, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543223" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">20B</figureCitation>
) with minute, central translucent round spots that look like rudimentary lanterns. Sternum VIII with posterior margin bisinuose. Pygidium (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. Costalampys quadriguttata (Gorham) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antenna, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Sternum IX, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543223" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">20H</figureCitation>
) with sides rounded, posterior corners weakly developed, posterior margin variably rounded to almost straight. Syntergite (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. Costalampys quadriguttata (Gorham) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antenna, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Sternum IX, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543223" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">20I,J</figureCitation>
) with anterior margin mildly curved. Phallus (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. Costalampys quadriguttata (Gorham) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antenna, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Sternum IX, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543223" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">20K-M</figureCitation>
) with dorsal plate almost straight in lateral view, with sides straight and acuminate at apical half. Paramere apex curved ventrally, ventral projection (lateral view) weakly developed, angle rounded. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Female</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. Costalampys quadriguttata (Gorham) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antenna, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Sternum IX, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543223" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">20C,D</figureCitation>
). Total length = 14.5 mm; Pronotal length = 2.6 mm; Pronotal width = 4.4 mm; Elytral length = 9.6 mm; Elytral width = 3.1 mm. Antennomeres III-X with apical corners projected, pointed, sterna VI (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. Costalampys quadriguttata (Gorham) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antenna, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Sternum IX, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543223" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">20D</figureCitation>
) lanterns small, occupying the central 1.4 of sternum, not reaching anterior margin, sternum VII (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. Costalampys quadriguttata (Gorham) comb. nov. A, Male habitus, dorsal view; B, Male habitus, ventral view; C, Female habitus, dorsal view; D, Female habitus, ventral view; E, Male antenna, lateral view; F, Male pronotum, dorsal view; G, Sternum IX, ventral view; H, Pygidium, dorsal view; I, Syntergite, dorsal view; J, Sternum IX, Ventral view; K, Aedeagus, dorsal view; L, Aedeagus, lateral view; M, Aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bar: 2 mm (A-D); Scale bar: 1.0 mm (E-M)." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e67185.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/543223" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">20D</figureCitation>
) with a feeble lighter spot, possibly a rudimentary lantern.
</paragraph>
