<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="115" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-2311.1880.tb02016.x" author="Gorham, HS" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" pagination="1 - 36" refId="B21" refString="Gorham, HS, 1880. I. Materials for a revision of the Lampyridae. Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London 28: 1 - 36, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-2311.1880.tb02016.x" title="I. Materials for a revision of the Lampyridae." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-2311.1880.tb02016.x" volume="28" year="1880">Gorham (1880)</bibRefCitation>
<taxonomicName authorityName="da Silveira &amp; Roza &amp; Vaz &amp; Mermudes" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="da Silveira &amp; Roza &amp; Vaz &amp; Mermudes" baseAuthorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Lucidota" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lucidota quadriguttata" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadriguttata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Lucidota quadriguttata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Bahia, Brazil: The author 
<normalizedToken originalValue="didn’t">didn't</normalizedToken>
give an explicit etymology for the species, but we assume it was based on the Latin word for &quot;with four spots&quot;, referring to its color pattern. 
<taxonomicName authority="Silveira, Roza, Vaz &amp; Mermudes, 2021-14" authorityName="da Silveira &amp; Roza &amp; Vaz &amp; Mermudes" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Gorham" baseAuthorityYear="1880" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Costalampys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Costalampys quadriguttata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadriguttata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Costalampys quadriguttata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Gorham, 1880) 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">comb. nov.</emphasis>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. bisbinotata" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="bisbinotata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">C. bisbinotata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Pic, 1943) 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">comb. nov.</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. capixaba" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="capixaba">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">C. capixaba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">sp. nov.</emphasis>
in the pronotal color pattern (overall dark brown; pronotal disc dark brown, lacking vittae, pronotal expansions somewhat translucent anteriorly, almost entirely pale yellow, except by posterior margin, which is outlined in brown, blending with the dark brown disc color), but differs from both in having the pygidium, as well as sterna VIII and IX, entirely translucent in both sexes (dark brown in both sexes of 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. capixaba" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="capixaba">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">C. capixaba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">sp. nov.</emphasis>
, partially translucent in 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. bisbinotata" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" rank="species" species="bisbinotata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">C. bisbinotata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Pic, 1943) 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">comb. nov.</emphasis>
males, entirely dark brown in females), and sternum VII with a medial translucent spot in males (absent in the other species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="115">
<taxonomicName authority="Silveira, Roza, Vaz &amp; Mermudes, 2021-14" authorityName="da Silveira &amp; Roza &amp; Vaz &amp; Mermudes" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Gorham" baseAuthorityYear="1880" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Costalampys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Costalampys quadriguttata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadriguttata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">Costalampys quadriguttata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Gorham, 1880) 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="115">comb. nov.</emphasis>
was previously reported for the Brazilian State of Bahia. 
<bibRefCitation author="Olivier, E" journalOrPublisher="Revue d'Entomologie (Caen)" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" pagination="1 - 8" refId="B41" refString="Olivier, E, 1886. Lampyrides nouveaux ou peu connus du Musee de Leyde. Revue d'Entomologie (Caen) 5: 1 - 8" title="Lampyrides nouveaux ou peu connus du Musee de Leyde." volume="5" year="1886">Olivier (1886)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned specimens collected by E. Gounelle in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Salobro”">&quot;Salobro&quot;</normalizedToken>
, currently Canavieiras, BA (cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Aguiar, PC" journalOrPublisher="Revista Geografica de America Central" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" pagination="189 - 216" refId="B1" refString="Aguiar, PC, Bruno-Lima, N, Moreau-Souza-dos-Santos, AM, Fontes-de-Oliveira, E, 2014. Evolucao da ocupacao e na configuracao territorial do Municipio de Canavieiras, Bahia, Brasil. Revista Geografica de America Central 2: 189 - 216" title="Evolucao da ocupacao e na configuracao territorial do Municipio de Canavieiras, Bahia, Brasil." volume="2" year="2014">Aguiar et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
), which we found in his collection at MNHN (see below). Pierre 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Émile">Emile</normalizedToken>
Gounelle was an engineer and entomologist who worked for the French Ministry of the Colonies, and traveled to Brazil on several occasions (
<bibRefCitation author="Papavero, N" journalOrPublisher="de Sao Paulo, Museu de Zoologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" refId="B48" refString="Papavero, N, 1971. 1 Essays on the history of Neotropical dipterology: with special reference to collectors (1750-1905). Univ. de Sao Paulo, Museu de Zoologia" title="1 Essays on the history of Neotropical dipterology: with special reference to collectors (1750 - 1905). Univ." year="1971">Papavero 1971</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Lourteig, A" journalOrPublisher="Brittonia" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" pagination="264 - 265" refId="B27" refString="Lourteig, A, 1986. The botanical collections of Pierre-Emile Gounelle. Brittonia 38: 264 - 265" title="The botanical collections of Pierre-Emile Gounelle." volume="38" year="1986">Lourteig 1986</bibRefCitation>
). On his first trip, among other places, Gounelle visited 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Salobro”">&quot;Salobro&quot;</normalizedToken>
between June and July, 1885 (
<bibRefCitation author="Papavero, N" journalOrPublisher="de Sao Paulo, Museu de Zoologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" refId="B48" refString="Papavero, N, 1971. 1 Essays on the history of Neotropical dipterology: with special reference to collectors (1750-1905). Univ. de Sao Paulo, Museu de Zoologia" title="1 Essays on the history of Neotropical dipterology: with special reference to collectors (1750 - 1905). Univ." year="1971">Papavero 1971</bibRefCitation>
), which was a popular destination for its diamond mines at that time (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Aguiar, PC" journalOrPublisher="Revista Geografica de America Central" pageId="0" pageNumber="115" pagination="189 - 216" refId="B1" refString="Aguiar, PC, Bruno-Lima, N, Moreau-Souza-dos-Santos, AM, Fontes-de-Oliveira, E, 2014. Evolucao da ocupacao e na configuracao territorial do Municipio de Canavieiras, Bahia, Brasil. Revista Geografica de America Central 2: 189 - 216" title="Evolucao da ocupacao e na configuracao territorial do Municipio de Canavieiras, Bahia, Brasil." volume="2" year="2014">Aguiar et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
). Here, we expand the known range of the species to the State of Pernambuco, and also give more detailed locality data within the state of Bahia.
</paragraph>
